      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The Supreme Court's interpretation of the Second Amendment is a massive, ongoing legal and political debate, not a settled matter of pure historical fact. Proponents of the current rulings argue they are faithfully applying the text and history of the founding era. Conversely, critics see modern interpretations as judicial activism, expanding rights beyond what the Founders intended. Ultimately, the \"correct\" view depends entirely on which constitutional theory—originalism or living constitutionalism—you choose to support.",
      "source": "target",
